name: On top of the world
description:
At over 2,653m above sea level, the Weisshorn is the highest peak in the Arosa region that can be reached by cable car. From where this panorama was taken, there are breathtaking views of more than 400 mountain peaks in Switzerland and neighbouring countries to enjoy. 

Arosa is a town and a municipality in the Plessur Region in the canton of Graubünden in Switzerland. It is both a summer and a winter tourist resort and has received major boosts in popularity in the past due to famous fans including Sir Arthur Conan Doyle and Erwin Schrödinger; who was on holiday in Arosa during Christmas in 1925 when he made his breakthrough discovery of wave mechanics.  

This image is the result of five separate photos stitched together in photoshop. All five photos were taken on a Pentax K10D and other than the stitching, no other edits were made to the image. 

The full image dimensions are: W - 16100 x H - 2246 at 200 PPI.
